snippet.textDisplay:
Stay safe and happy BTS!
I'm saying this cause I can see and feel the disappointment and sadness in your eyes, in your voice. It feels terrible, not just as an ARMY, but as a normal human being to see you guys work so hard and yet you're unable to promote your album and perform in front of people who love and admire you. But if BTS is safe and happy then us ARMY becomes happier.
It is okay to be eager for something you've worked so hard for, then being disappointed and sad because things didn't happen the way they should be, but right now everyone is facing this situation. You're not walking alone. Better days will come again and till then let's not break down and stay bulletproof together. I love you guys. 💜
